[Portrait]Chocobo Defense[Dialog]
Fovoham's chocobos face poaching on a scale never before
seen. If naught is done, their population will fall to levels
from which they cannot hope to recover. Please, save the
birds from these soulless poachers before the sound of
warking is forever lost to the windflats!
[spazio][spazio]-Society for the Protection of Endangered Wildfowl
u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]Chicken Race[Dialog]
We are conducting a test of courage in the form of a
fenland race. Should you wish to prove your mettle, join
us at your own peril.
[spazio][spazio]-Lionheart Adventurers


u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]Treasure Hunt[Dialog]
An item of no small importance appears to have fallen
from its wagon sometime during our last journey. Any
man, woman, or child who returns it to us before brigands
claim it as their own will be handsomely rewarded.
[spazio][spazio]-Gallionne Caravans

u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]Teioh[Dialog]
Every hunter has heard tell of Teioh, the fastest black
chocobo alive. Many a hunter has tried his hand at capturing
the elusive bird, but as of yet, none have prevailed. We
seek the ones who can.
[spazio][spazio]-Fraternal Order of Huntsmen

u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]Lost Heirloom[Dialog]
Foulest fortune! My most prized family heirloom, Saint
Ajora's Tear, was stolen by cowardly rogues. Would that
some honorable knights might retrieve it for me! Failing
that, dishonorable sellswords would do.
[spazio][spazio]-Count Thanes

u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]The Fete[Dialog]
You are cordially invited to attend our evening fete. Enjoy
such hospitality as you have never seen! There will be a
rousing performance, with an exhilarating climax just for
you. We do so hope that you will come.
[spazio][spazio]-Swirling Silks Dance Troupe

u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]Desert Minefield[Dialog]
I've a need to cross the desert, but with the abundance of
those blasted bombs, I would not dare set foot there
alone. I seek a learned guide to escort me on my way.
[spazio][spazio]-Govis


u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]Littering[Dialog]
I am plagued at every hour of the day. Some damnable fools
persist in lobbing dangerous items into my courtyard from
the overlooking rooftops. Would there were a peaceful
solution to the problem, but I fear enlisting the aid of
warriors is my only choice.
[spazio][spazio]-Count Hattori
u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]Shades of the Past[Dialog]
I am an exorcist attempting to banish spirits with a
particularly strong attachment to this world. My every
attempt to exorcise them has met with failure, and there
is little more I can do. I await men or women capable of
dealing with ghosts in a less...sophisticated manner.
[spazio][spazio]-Master Sampson
u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]The Knights Templar[Dialog]
We seek the strong and pious to serve the gods' will as
sworn members of the Knights Templar. Prove your
martial prowess by crossing swords with our ranks, and
you may well find yourself among them.
[spazio][spazio]-Mullonde Church of Glabados

u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]All-Star Melee[Dialog]
A group of ne'er-do-wells has been terrorizing the city,
but such is their strength and cunning that we have yet
been unable to quell them. Rich reward awaits those who
bring these blackguards to justice.
[spazio][spazio]-Gariland City Guard

u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]The Guarded Temple[Dialog]
There is a temple said to house an artefact of unparalleled
value, but the temple's fearsome guardians have foiled all
previous attempts to retrieve it. We are in search of
stalwart steel to defeat the guardians and claim the holy
treasure.
[spazio][spazio]-League of Treasure Hunters
u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]Nightmares[Dialog]
I have scary dreams every time I go to sleep. I make
water in my beddings and Mother scolds me each morn.
Please, make them go away!
[spazio][spazio]-Little Jack


u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]Brave Story[Dialog]
The end to this story is not yet written. There are others
with roles to play, and their tales, too, can now be told.
Come, that I might enlighten you with the truth.
[spazio][spazio]-Edell, Orbonne Monastery Gardener


u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}

[Portrait]An Ill Wind[Dialog]
An unearthly wind howls through the ruins of Ziekden
Fortress, chilling grown men to their marrow. Mayhap
it's naught more than superstitious fear, but we offer
a reward to any who would investigate nonetheless.
[spazio][spazio]-Eagrose Castle Guard

u(Press [Croce] to accept mission.){END}
